main event: On September 23, 1967, two unidentified flying objects were observed in Milford, Ohio at 9:30 p.m.
interesting points: The sighting involved two objects observed visually,The conclusion from the Civil Defense stated it was an unknown incident,The agent conducting radar bomb scores was unaware of any related incidents until much later,The radar used by the agent was described as old and not very effective,No photographs were included in the report.
witness description: not applicable as no confirmed witnesses were noted
